Florham Park Preschool Program -our schools are open and ready to welcome new faces! Seats are still available for students who are aged on or before 4 as of October 1, 2020 who reside in Florham Park or the surrounding area!

Available seats are in our half-day preschool program which operates from 8:35 am to 11 am, five days per week. Our program is taught by an experienced, certified educator, and supported by qualified assistants, using the highly engaging "Creative Curriculum".

Please see the attached flyer for more information or fill out the preliminary application form here: https://forms.gle/1TSHiGd1qDg2d2AV6. Seats will be filled on a first come, first served basis.

post_text: Congratulations! The Florham Park School District just received incredible news from the NJDOE that following this year's NJQSAC monitoring, the Florham Park School District scored a 90% or above in all 5 NJQSAC areas (Instruction & Programming, Fiscal Management, Governance, Operations, Personnel) and has been designated as a “high performing” district in NJ. Congratulations to the Board of Education, Administration, Staff, Students, Parents and Community!
text: Congratulations! Congratulations to the Board of Education, Administration, Staff, Students, Parents and Community!

post_text: The district and the Special Services Department is excited to provide you with this in-depth, 45 minute training video "Tips & Strategies for Family-Student Wellness" presented by our school counselors on varying counseling topics that could assist you and your family with the digital learning environment and experience, spanning from functional workspace creations to social-emotional components, such as tips for managing anxiety and speaking with your children about society's current situation. We strongly encourage you to view the list of topics being covered which will be presented following the brief video introduction. Your child and family's social-emotional wellbeing is just as important to us as your child's academic progress.

post_text: For the past few weeks, the Florham Park School District has been preemptively planning for the NJDOE to provide a “Distance Learning” option for schools should a health-related school closing occur. Being proactive, the District has already conducted meetings with key stakeholders; including but not limited to, the tech department, team leaders, grade level teaching teams, the administration, the board of education and county/state officials. In addition, today’s faculty meetings in each school were dedicated towards the Distance Learning platform. Therefore, though you may read of other districts that have limited their instructional day to include an early dismissal or delayed opening to plan with their staff, the Florham Park School District is pleased to report to our parents and community that our district has already had these preemptive planning meetings, and we will continue to, in order to best prepare should a school closing occur. Thank you to the staff and administration for all of their hard work and dedication!
text: For the past few weeks, the Florham Park School District has been preemptively planning for the NJDOE to provide a “Distance Learning” option for schools should a health-related school closing occur. Being proactive, the District has already conducted meetings with key stakeholders; including but not limited to, the tech department, team leaders, grade level teaching teams, the administration, the board of education and county/state officials. In addition, today’s faculty meetings in each school were dedicated towards the Distance Learning platform. Therefore, though you may read of other districts that have limited their instructional day to include an early dismissal or delayed opening to plan with their staff, the Florham Park School District is pleased to report to our parents and community that our district has already had these preemptive planning meetings, and we will continue to, in order to best prepare should a school closing occur. Thank you to the staff and administration for all of their hard work and dedication!

post_text: Briarwood School student enjoyed a beautiful day outside during our Jump-a-thon! Our students did a wonderful job jumping and breaking their personal jumping records! post_text:
Congratulations Brooklake School Music Program! BKL just received national recognition for a music merit award from the NAMM Foundation. Kuddos to our our music teachers, Mr. Hipwell and Mr. Serfozo, to the students, staff, parents, and Board of Education members for your continued support of music and the arts!
https://www.nammfoundation.org/articles/bcme-2019-schools

post_text:
Unlock The Box Video - Critical Thinking - Brooklake School Gr.5 - This video shows Mr. Letchinger’s Gr.5 math class fully engaged and working on the "Unlock the Box” activity. This is an interdisciplinary activity that involves elements of math and social studies, along with critical thinking skills and teamwork, needed to decipher the clues necessary to unlock each of the four locks on the box.
